00:48:05,341 --> 00:48:08,397
布莱尔一家已经许诺如果我们听取这些人的谈判，他们会支持这次修正案
The Blairs have promised support for the
amendment if we listen to these people.

733
00:48:08,433 --> 00:48:10,299
哦，布莱尔说了啊，是吗？
Oh, the Blairs promise, do they?

734
00:48:10,316 --> 00:48:12,663
你觉得我们听完这个谈判然后拒绝掉
You think they’ll keep their promise
once we have heard these delegates

735
00:48:12,679 --> 00:48:14,646
他们还会说话算话吗？我们必须这样做
and refused them?
Which we will have to do,

736
00:48:14,666 --> 00:48:19,314
因为他们的提案几乎肯定会说要保留他们的奴隶！
since their proposal most certainly will
be predicated on keeping their slaves!

737
00:48:19,370 --> 00:48:22,098
威廉，民主党那边的选票还有多少把握
What hope for any
Democratic votes, Willum,

738
00:48:22,222 --> 00:48:25,472
如果已经有传言说我拒绝了这次结束战争的机会？
if word gets out that I’ve
refused a chance to end the war?

739
00:48:26,275 --> 00:48:30,370
你觉得消息不会走漏吗？这是华盛顿啊
You think word won’t get out?
In Washington?

740
00:48:32,134 --> 00:48:35,931
这个修正案和联合的和平谈判，二者不可兼得
It’s either the amendment or this
Confederate peace, you cannot have both.

741
00:48:37,254 --> 00:48:39,656
“假若你能预知将来
“If you can look into the seeds of time,

742
00:48:40,657 --> 00:48:43,907
预测这粒种子会发芽而那粒不会，那就请向我直言...”
and say which grain will grow and
which will not, speak then to me...”

743
00:48:45,112 --> 00:48:46,751
噢，灾难，这真是灾难
SEWARD: Oh, disaster.
This is a disaster!

744
00:48:46,785 --> 00:48:49,105
时间是很好的抚慰，Willum
LINCOLN: Time is a great
thickener of things, Willum.

745
00:48:49,129 --> 00:48:51,014
我猜也是
Yes, I suppose it is.

746
00:48:51,280 --> 00:48:53,879
其实我没听懂你刚才什么意思
Actually I have no idea
what you mean by that.

747
00:48:55,472 --> 00:48:57,274
给我再找13张选票
Get me thirteen votes.

748
00:48:58,260 --> 00:49:00,940
里士满的人现在还没到
Them fellers from Richmond ain’t here yit.

749
00:49:21,781 --> 00:49:24,183
半数的波士顿男人都参军了！
ROBERT: You drafted
half the men in Boston!

750
00:49:24,363 --> 00:49:26,766
你觉得他们的家人会怎么看我？
What do you think their
families think about me?

751
00:49:27,078 --> 00:49:29,234
他们唯一没有朝我扔东西吐痰的原因是
The only reason they don’t
throw things and spit on me

752
00:49:29,254 --> 00:49:30,603
是因为你太有名了
is ‘cause you’re so popular.

753
00:49:30,814 --> 00:49:34,753
我无法专心学习英国重商主义法律
I can’t concentrate on-on
British mercantile law,

754
00:49:34,761 --> 00:49:37,262
我也对英国重商主义法律没兴趣
I don’t care about British mercantile law.

755
00:49:38,988 --> 00:49:40,644
我甚至可能都不想当律师
I might not even want to be a lawyer.

756
00:49:42,384 --> 00:49:44,786
这会是铁饭碗
It’s a sturdy profession,

757
00:49:45,225 --> 00:49:46,502
也会很有用
and a useful one.

758
00:49:46,517 --> 00:49:51,057
是，我想成为有用的人，但是要现在，不是以后！
Yes, and I want to be useful,
but now, not afterwards!

759
00:49:51,140 --> 00:49:53,983
我不想穿这些，Slade先生，从来都不合身
I ain’t wearing them things,
Mr. Slade, they never fit right.

760
00:49:54,019 --> 00:49:56,387
夫人会让您穿的，别想着不穿的事了
The missus will have you wear ‘em.
Don’t think about leaving ‘em.

761
00:49:56,418 --> 00:49:58,771
你又在拖延了，你最喜欢的策略
You’re delaying,
that’s your favorite tactic.

762
00:49:58,881 --> 00:50:02,515
你不会告诉我不许，但战争一个月之内就要结束了，你知道会结束的！
You won’t tell me no, but the war will be
over in a month, and you know it will!

763
00:50:02,563 --> 00:50:09,505
我发现当预言家是一个相当不好预言的职业
LINCOLN: I’ve found that prophesying is
one of life’s less prophet-able occupations.

764
00:50:11,214 --> 00:50:13,448
为什么有些奴隶比其他的贵？
TAD: Why do some slaves
cost more than others?

765
00:50:13,498 --> 00:50:16,123
如果他们年轻、健康，女性还能生孩子
Ah, if they’re still young and healthy,
if the women can still conceive,

766
00:50:16,150 --> 00:50:19,153
- 就值更多的钱
- 放回盒子里去，你这小坏蛋
- they’ll pay more.
–Put ‘em back in the box, you scoundrel.

767
00:50:20,724 --> 00:50:23,733
我们后天就把它们还给Gardner先生
We’ll return them to Mr. Gardner’s
studio day after next.

768
00:50:25,223 --> 00:50:27,418
小心一点拿
Be careful with‘em, now.

769
00:50:27,868 --> 00:50:29,711
这个皮还是呆在牛身上比较好
These things should’ve stayed on the calf.

770
00:50:29,743 --> 00:50:33,932
TAD: When you were a slave,
Mr. Slade, did they beat you?
TAD: 当你是一个奴隶的时候，
Mr. Slade,他们打你了吗？

771
00:50:34,065 --> 00:50:35,806
SLADE: I was born a free man.
SLADE: 我出生就是一个自由民。

772
00:50:35,899 --> 00:50:38,712
Nobody beat me except
I beat them right back.
没有人能打我除了我打他们。

773
00:50:40,615 --> 00:50:42,262
Mr. Lincoln, could you come with me...
林肯先生，你能跟我来一下吗....

774
00:50:42,282 --> 00:50:45,643
Mrs. Keckley was a slave.
Ask her if she was beaten.
Mrs. Keckley曾经是一个奴隶。
问她是否被殴打。

775
00:50:46,030 --> 00:50:47,504
– TAD: Were you?
– Tad!
– TAD: 是你？
– Tad!

776
00:50:48,210 --> 00:50:50,742
MRS. KEKLEY: I was beaten with a fire
shovel when I was younger than you.
当我还很小的时间，我曾经被一个火铲殴打。

777
00:50:50,778 --> 00:50:53,466
You should go to Mrs. Lincoln.
She’s in Willie’s room.
你应该去找林肯太太。
她正在Willie的房间里面。

778
00:50:54,568 --> 00:50:55,531
ROBERT: She never goes in there.
ROBERT:她从来没有去过那里。

779
00:50:55,563 --> 00:50:58,258
JOHN HAY: The reception line
is already stretching out the door.
JOHN HAY: 招待会已经在门外准备了。

780
00:51:01,920 --> 00:51:04,208
See, I’ll be the only man over
fifteen and under sixty-five
看，我将是唯一一个在15到65之间的男人

781
00:51:04,235 --> 00:51:06,485
in this whole place not in uniform.
在这个地方没有穿制服的。

782
00:51:06,548 --> 00:51:07,932
I’m under fifteen.
我还没有15岁。

783
00:51:28,685 --> 00:51:31,088
MARY: My head hurts so.
MARY: 我的头好痛。

784
00:51:34,221 --> 00:51:36,822
I prayed for death
the night Willie died.
我祈祷今晚 Willie去死。

785
00:51:37,960 --> 00:51:40,963
The headaches are how
I know I didn’t get my wish.
头痛怎么样了
我知道我没有实现我的愿望。

786
00:51:43,917 --> 00:51:48,904
How to endure the long afternoon
that go deep into the night.
怎么去忍受从下午一直到深夜。

787
00:51:48,947 --> 00:51:50,000
LINCOLN: I know.
LINCOLN:我知道。

788
00:51:50,160 --> 00:51:53,481
Trying not to think about him.
How will I manage?
试着不去想他。
我将如何管理？

789
00:51:53,531 --> 00:51:55,624
– Somehow you will.
– Somehow.
– 你将会找到办法。
–怎么办。

790
00:51:57,530 --> 00:52:00,533
MARY: Somehow. Somehow. Somehow...
MARY: 怎么办。怎么办。怎么办...

791
00:52:00,783 --> 00:52:03,636
MARY: Every party, every...
MARY:没一个党派，每一个...

792
00:52:07,240 --> 00:52:08,642
And now...
那么...

793
00:52:09,819 --> 00:52:14,204
Four years more in this
terrible house... reproaching us.
在这个糟糕的地方已经4年多了...责备我们把。

794
00:52:16,268 --> 00:52:18,477
He was a very sick little boy.
他是一个生病的小男孩，

795
00:52:18,517 --> 00:52:21,173
We should’ve cancelled
that reception, shouldn’t we?
我们将推掉欢迎会，不是吗？

796
00:52:21,202 --> 00:52:24,129
– We didn’t know how sick he was.
– I knew, I knew...
-我们不知道他怎么生病了。
-我知道，我知道...

797
00:52:25,232 --> 00:52:27,635
I saw that night he was dying.
我看见那天晚上他快要死了.

798
00:52:27,699 --> 00:52:33,572
Three years ago, the war was going
so badly, and we had to put on a face.
3年前，战争正在进行
非常的糟糕，我们不得不装装样子。

799
00:52:33,918 --> 00:52:37,169
– But I... saw Willie was dying.
– Molly.
-但是我...看见Willie快要死了。
-Molly。

800
00:52:37,212 --> 00:52:38,600
– I saw him.
– Listen.
-我看见他.
-听着。

801
00:52:41,486 --> 00:52:43,844
LINCLON: It’s too hard.
林肯： 这太难了。

802
00:52:48,862 --> 00:52:50,264
LINCOLN: Too hard.
林肯：太难了。

803
00:53:12,248 --> 00:53:15,233
WILLIAM SLADE: She’s just ten
feet yonder. I’d like to keep my job.
WILLIAM SLADE:她离那里只有10英尺远。我想保住我的工作。

804
00:53:16,979 --> 00:53:20,253
MARY: Senator Sumner,
it has been much too long.
MARY: Sumner参议员,
它已经太长了。

805
00:53:20,319 --> 00:53:22,506
CHARLES SUMNER: “Oh, who can
look on that celestial face and..."
CHARLES SUMNER: 喔，谁能看着天空中的脸..."

806
00:53:22,526 --> 00:53:24,102
– And...?
– James Ashley, ma’am,
-然后...?
– James Ashley, 女士，

807
00:53:24,117 --> 00:53:26,400
– we’ve met several times.
– Praise Heavens, praise Heavens,
-我们已经见过好几次了。
-赞美上帝，赞美上帝。

808
00:53:26,437 --> 00:53:28,703
just when I had abandoned
hope of amusement,
就在我已经放弃了希望的时候，

809
00:53:28,713 --> 00:53:31,115
it’s the Chairman of the House Ways
and Means Committee!
这是众议院筹款委员会的主席！

810
00:53:31,291 --> 00:53:32,432
THADDEUS STEVENS:
Mrs. Lincoln.
THADDEUS STEVENS:
林肯夫人。

811
00:53:32,587 --> 00:53:34,989
Madame President if you please.
主席夫人，如果你请.

812
00:53:35,224 --> 00:53:40,023
Oh, don’t convene another
subcommittee to investigate me, sir!
哦，别在召集其他的小组委员会来调查我了，先生！

813
00:53:40,043 --> 00:53:41,831
I’m teasing! Smile, Senator Wade.
我开玩笑的！笑一个， Wade参议员。

814
00:53:41,849 --> 00:53:43,926
I believe I am smiling, Mrs. Lincoln.
我想我正在笑，林肯夫人.

815
00:53:43,974 --> 00:53:46,875
STEVENS: As long as your household
accounts are in order, Madame,
STEVENS: 只要你的家庭账户是合法的，女士，

816
00:53:46,954 --> 00:53:49,357
we’ll have no need to investigate them.
我们将不需要去调查他们。

817
00:53:49,420 --> 00:53:52,397
You have always taken such a lively,
你的行为总是这样的有趣的，

818
00:53:52,464 --> 00:53:56,338
even prosecutorial interest
in my household accounts.
甚至对我的家庭账户有起诉的兴趣。

819
00:53:56,378 --> 00:53:58,780
Your household accounts
have always been so interesting.
你的家庭账户总是这样的有趣。

820
00:53:58,928 --> 00:54:01,331
Yes, thank you, it’s true,
是啊 ，谢谢你，这是正确的，

821
00:54:01,600 --> 00:54:04,002
the miracles I have wrought out
我已经找出了一些惊人的事情

822
00:54:04,061 --> 00:54:08,048
of fertilizer bills and cutlery
invoices, but I had to!
化肥票据和餐具发票，但是我不得不！

823
00:54:09,620 --> 00:54:13,231
Four years ago, when the President
and I arrived, this was pure pigsty.
五年前，当总统和我到这里的时候，这里完全就是一个猪圈。

824
00:54:13,309 --> 00:54:15,144
Tobacco stains in the turkey carpets.
烟草污染了这些土耳其地毯。

825
00:54:15,171 --> 00:54:18,507
Mushrooms, green as the moon,
sprouting from the ceilings!
蘑菇，绿的就像是月亮，
从天花板上发芽！

826
00:54:18,621 --> 00:54:21,911
And a pauper’s pittance
allotted for improvements.
仅仅分配了一点穷光蛋的微薄金额来改善它。

827
00:54:22,237 --> 00:54:25,659
As if your committee joined
with all of Washington awaiting,
就好像你们的委员会在华盛顿的办事处一样，

828
00:54:25,686 --> 00:54:29,258
in what you anticipated
would be our comfort in squalor,
在你们预期的，我们将舒适的生活在邋塌的环境里面，

829
00:54:29,802 --> 00:54:33,694
further proof that my husband
and I were prairie primitives,
进一步的证明，我的丈夫和我都是大草原的原始人，

830
00:54:34,031 --> 00:54:36,953
unsuited to the position
to which an error of the people,
我们不适应这个位置，可能对人民造成一些错误，

831
00:54:36,988 --> 00:54:40,410
a flaw in the democratic process,
had elevated us.
在民主进程中的一些瑕疵，我们是可以被原谅的。

832
00:54:40,838 --> 00:54:43,768
The past is the past,
it’s a new year now,
过去的已经过去了，
现在是新的一年了，

833
00:54:43,858 --> 00:54:47,837
and we are all getting along,
or so they tell me.
我们都在一起前进，
或者他们告诉我。

834
00:54:48,120 --> 00:54:50,197
I gather we are working together!
我聚集我们在一起工作！

835
00:54:50,349 --> 00:54:54,007
The White House and the other House,
hatching little plans together.
白宫和一些其他的机构，都将给计划带来一些小小的阴影。

836
00:54:54,049 --> 00:54:54,836
– ROBERT: Mother?
– What?
– ROBERT: 妈妈？
– 什么？

837
00:54:54,875 --> 00:54:56,629
– You’re creating a bottleneck.
– Oh!
-你制造了一个颈瓶。
-噢！

838
00:54:57,074 --> 00:54:59,167
MARY: Oh, I’m detaining you.
MARY: 噢，我要扣留你。

839
00:54:59,641 --> 00:55:02,782
And more importantly,
the people behind you.
更重要的是，
你身后的人。

840
00:55:03,168 --> 00:55:06,082
How the people love my husband,
你知道人民多么的热爱我的丈夫，

841
00:55:06,363 --> 00:55:10,661
they flock to see him by
their thousands on public days!
在公共日，他们成群结队去看望他！

842
00:55:10,852 --> 00:55:13,255
They will never love you
the way they love him.
他们将用从没有爱你的方式去热爱他。

843
00:55:15,178 --> 00:55:17,581
How difficult it must be
for you to know that.
这必须是多么的困难你知道。

844
00:55:18,457 --> 00:55:20,859
And yet how important to remember it.
但是更重要的是去记住他。

845
00:55:31,482 --> 00:55:34,476
Since we have the floor
next in the debate,
自从我们在下一个讨论中得到发言权，

846
00:55:34,502 --> 00:55:36,904
I thought I’d suggest you might...
我想我应该建议你...

847
00:55:37,468 --> 00:55:42,494
temper your contributions so as not
to frighten our conservative friends?
控制你的贡献和脾气，只要别吓到我们哪些保守的朋友？

848
00:55:42,599 --> 00:55:46,569
STEVENS: Ashley insists you’re ensuring
approval by dispensing patronage
STEVENS:Ashley 坚决要求你确保赞同去支持

849
00:55:46,629 --> 00:55:49,632
to otherwise undeserving Democrats.
否则不配民主党。

850
00:55:49,687 --> 00:55:52,732
LINCOLN: I can’t ensure a single damn
thing if you scare the whole House
林肯：我不能确保这个该死的事情即使你恐吓整个议院

851
00:55:52,772 --> 00:55:57,102
with talk of land appropriations,
revolutionary tribunals, punitive...
用土地拨款的讨论，革命特别法院，.....

852
00:55:57,134 --> 00:55:59,720
STEVENS: When the war ends,
I intend to push for
STEVENS: 当战争结束的时候，我就打算去争取

853
00:55:59,773 --> 00:56:04,388
full equality, the Negro vote,
and much more.
完全平等，黑人的表决权，以及一些其他的。

854
00:56:05,018 --> 00:56:08,253
Congress shall mandate the seizure
of every foot of rebel land
国会应该授权查封反叛政府的每一个地方

855
00:56:08,302 --> 00:56:11,021
and every dollar of their property.
和他们财产的每一个硬币。

856
00:56:12,346 --> 00:56:14,589
We’ll use their confiscated
wealth to establish
我们应该使用它们被充公的财产去建立

857
00:56:14,616 --> 00:56:17,334
hundreds of thousands
of free Negro farmers,
成百上千的自由黑人农场，

858
00:56:17,362 --> 00:56:20,159
and at their side soldiers armed to occupy
并对在他们那边的士兵进行武装占领

859
00:56:20,187 --> 00:56:22,701
and transform the heritage of traitors.
并且改造那些叛徒的遗产。

860
00:56:23,718 --> 00:56:25,005
We’ll build up a land down there
我们将在那里建立一个高地

861
00:56:25,033 --> 00:56:28,235
of free men and free women
and free children and freedom.
为了那些自由的男人，女人和孩子们。

862
00:56:29,977 --> 00:56:32,380
The nation needs to know
that we have such plans.
这个国家需要知道我们有这样的计划。

863
00:56:33,928 --> 00:56:36,931
That’s the untempered
version of reconstruction.
这个是这个重建物没有改造的版本。

864
00:56:38,923 --> 00:56:43,474
LINCOLN: It’s not... It’s not
quite exactly what I intend,
林肯：这不是...这不是准确上来说这不是我想要的，

865
00:56:45,504 --> 00:56:48,965
but we shall oppose one
another in the course of time.
当时我们将来随着时间的推移，可能会反对其他的。

866
00:56:49,178 --> 00:56:51,328
Now we’re working together,
and I’m asking you...
现在我们在一起工作，
那么我现在要请求你们....

867
00:56:51,369 --> 00:56:52,479
For patience, I expect.
能够坚持，我期望。

868
00:56:52,512 --> 00:56:55,458
LINCOLN: When the people disagree,
bringing them together requires
林肯：当民众不同意的时候，
把他们按照要求整合在一起

869
00:56:55,490 --> 00:56:57,138
going slow till they’re ready to make up.
减慢速度知道他们准备好。

870
00:56:57,180 --> 00:56:58,506
Ah, shit on the people,
噢，该死的民众，

871
00:56:58,517 --> 00:57:00,118
and what they want,
and what they’re ready for,
他们想要什么，
他们到底准备做什么，

872
00:57:00,136 --> 00:57:02,721
I don’t give a goddamn about
the people and what they want!
我根本不在乎这些民众，和他们想要的东西！

873
00:57:02,874 --> 00:57:05,671
This is the face of someone
who has fought long and hard
这就是一些人面对长期和艰苦的斗争

874
00:57:05,676 --> 00:57:08,596
for the good of the people
without caring much for any of ‘em.
为了人民的利益
没有去在意太多关于他们的。

875
00:57:09,686 --> 00:57:12,089
And I look a lot worse without my wig.
并且当我没有这个法官帽的时候，我看见了太多糟糕的事情

876
00:57:12,682 --> 00:57:16,122
The people elected me! To represent them!
人民选择了我！我代表他们！

877
00:57:16,296 --> 00:57:19,445
To lead them! And I lead!
You ought to try it!
去领导他们！
你应该去尝试做它！

878
00:57:21,662 --> 00:57:25,015
I admire your zeal, Mr. Stevens,
我赞扬你的热情，Mr. Stevens,

879
00:57:25,027 --> 00:57:28,230
and I have tried to profit
from the example of it.
并且我试图从它的一些样本中得。

880
00:57:29,915 --> 00:57:32,313
If I’d listened to you,
I’d’ve declared every slave free
如果我听从你的讲话，
我将宣布所有奴隶自由

881
00:57:32,326 --> 00:57:34,928
the minute the first shell
struck Fort Sumter.
这个第一份炮弹将会在萨穆特堡。

882
00:57:35,034 --> 00:57:37,644
Then the border states would’ve
gone over to the confederacy,
然后这些边境邦将不会倒向南部政府，

883
00:57:37,730 --> 00:57:40,255
the war would’ve been lost
and the Union along with it,
这个战争将会结束，
联盟将和它一道向前，

884
00:57:40,335 --> 00:57:44,102
and instead of abolishing slavery,
as we hope to do in two weeks,
而不是废除奴隶制度，
我们希望在两个星期之内完成它，

885
00:57:44,223 --> 00:57:46,809
we’d be watching helpless
as infants as it spread
由于它的传播，我们将看起来像婴儿那样软弱无助

886
00:57:46,830 --> 00:57:49,030
from the American South
into South America.
从美国南部到南美洲。

887
00:57:49,094 --> 00:57:51,504
STEVENS: Oh God, how you
have longed to say that to me.
STEVENS:噢，天哪，你怎么这么想对我说这些。

888
00:57:52,818 --> 00:57:57,069
You claim you trust them.
But you know what the people are.
你声称你信任他们。
但是你知道他们是什么人吗。

889
00:57:57,656 --> 00:58:03,106
You know that the inner compass
that should direct the soul toward justice
你知道，内心的指南针将引导我们的灵魂走向正义

890
00:58:03,210 --> 00:58:06,907
has ossified in white men
and women, north and south,
在南部和北部，那些白人男人和女人的思维已经僵化，

891
00:58:06,943 --> 00:58:10,874
unto utter uselessness
through tolerating the evil of slavery.
绝对无法承认通过该死的奴隶制度。

892
00:58:10,930 --> 00:58:13,540
White people cannot bear
the thought of sharing
白人无法忍受这种和黑人均分的观点

893
00:58:13,552 --> 00:58:16,332
this country’s infinite
abundance with Negroes.
这个国家里面充斥着大量的黑人。

894
00:58:19,231 --> 00:58:22,234
A compass, I learnt when
I was surveying, it’ll...
这个指南针，当我学会了测量，它将....

895
00:58:22,734 --> 00:58:25,859
it’ll point you True North
from where you’re standing,
它将在你站的地方为你指向真正的北方，

896
00:58:26,091 --> 00:58:28,918
but it’s got no advice about the swamps
但是它没法给你通知中途的沼泽

897
00:58:29,090 --> 00:58:32,653
and deserts and chasms that
you’ll encounter along the way.
沙漠和悬崖，
以及一些你可能在路上忽然遇到的困境。

898
00:58:33,266 --> 00:58:36,704
If in pursuit of your destination,
you plunge ahead, heedless of obstacles,
如果在追求你目的地的过程中，
你只顾向前，对阻碍不加注意，

899
00:58:36,710 --> 00:58:39,113
and achieve nothing more
than to sink in a swamp...
你不会比你直接沉没在沼泽里面得到更多...

900
00:58:41,616 --> 00:58:44,019
What’s the use of knowing True North?
你知道真正的北方有什么用处吗？

901
00:59:00,285 --> 00:59:04,060
LINCOLN: Robert’s gonna
plead with us to let him enlist.
林肯：Robert将要向我们恳求，允许他加入军队。

902
00:59:06,320 --> 00:59:08,352
Make time to talk to Robbie.
找个时间和Robbie谈谈。

903
00:59:08,493 --> 00:59:11,676
You only have time for Tad.
– But Tad’s young.
你只有时间花在Tad身上。
-但是Tad还很年轻。

904
00:59:12,190 --> 00:59:15,824
MARY: So is Robert.
Too young for the army.
MARY: 那么Robert呢.
他加入军队也太年轻了。

905
00:59:15,892 --> 00:59:18,895
Plenty of boys younger
than Robert signing up...
很多比Robert还要年轻的小伙子都加入了...

906
00:59:22,150 --> 00:59:23,712
Don’t take Robbie.
别想带走Robbie.

907
00:59:24,493 --> 00:59:26,399
Don’t let me lose my son.
不要让我失去我的儿子。

908
00:59:26,424 --> 00:59:27,388
[Knocking on door]

909
00:59:27,389 --> 00:59:30,246
Go away! We’re occupied!
走开！我们正忙！

910
00:59:33,943 --> 00:59:36,889
NICOLAY: Secretary Stanton has sent over
to tell you that as of half an hour ago,
NICOLAY: Stanton秘书已经在半个小时前派人过来叫你了，

911
00:59:36,909 --> 00:59:39,110
the shelling of Wilmington
harbor has commenced.
Wilmington港的炮击已经开始了。

912
00:59:44,311 --> 00:59:47,125
STANTON: They cannot possibly
maintain under this kind of an assault.
STANTON: 在这么猛烈的攻击下，他们不可能坚持下去。

913
00:59:47,274 --> 00:59:49,904
Terry’s got ten thousand men
surrounding the Goddamned fort,
Terry得到了10000名士兵包围了Goddamned堡，

914
00:59:49,907 --> 00:59:51,524
why doesn’t he answer my cables?
– WELLES: Fort Fisher
他为什么不回答我的电报？
– WELLES:费雪堡

915
00:59:51,540 --> 00:59:52,916
is a mountain of a building, Edwin.
是成堆的建筑，Edwin.

916
00:59:52,954 --> 00:59:54,214
MAJOR ECKERT: It’s the
largest fort they have, sir.
MAJOR ECKERT:这是他们拥有的最大的城堡，先生。

917
00:59:54,261 --> 00:59:55,744
WELLES: Twenty-two big
seacoast guns on each rampart.
WELLES: 22门巨大的海岸炮在城墙上面。

918
00:59:55,774 --> 00:59:57,613
MAJOR ECKERT: They’ve been
reinforcing it for the last two years
MAJOR ECKERT:在这最后2年里面，他们还不停地补强它。

919
00:59:57,636 --> 00:59:59,654
STANTON: They’ve taken 17,000
shells since yesterday!
STANTON: 他们从昨天起就用了17,000炮弹！

920
00:59:59,672 --> 01:00:03,717
I want to hear that Fort Fisher is ours
and Wilmington has fallen!
我希望听见费血堡是我们的了，并且Wilmington已经沦陷的消息！

921
01:00:03,805 --> 01:00:05,116
Send another damn cable!
给其他混蛋发送电报！

922
01:00:05,299 --> 01:00:07,916
The problem’s their
commander. Whiting!
问题是他们的指挥官。Whiting!

923
01:00:08,664 --> 01:00:11,375
He engineered the fortress himself.
The damned thing’s his child.
他亲自设计这个城堡。
这个该死的地方就像他的孩子。

924
01:00:11,410 --> 01:00:14,214
He’ll defend it till his every last man
is gone. He is not thinking...
他将保卫它，知道他的每一个士兵都阵亡。
他没有理智...

925
01:00:14,238 --> 01:00:15,714
LINCOLN (SHOUTING):
“Come on out, you old rat!”
林肯（大叫）：
 “出来，你这个老叛徒！”

926
01:00:19,586 --> 01:00:20,717
LINCOLN: That’s what...
林肯：那是什么....

927
01:00:20,887 --> 01:00:25,788
That' what Ethan Allen called to the
commander of Fort Ticonderogain in 1776.
那个就是在1776年被Ethan Allen称为Ticonderogain堡的指挥官。

928
01:00:25,830 --> 01:00:27,822
“Come on out, you old rat!”
“出来，你这个老叛徒！”

929
01:00:29,206 --> 01:00:32,879
Aah, ‘course there were only forty
odd redcoats at Ticonderoga.
啊哈，‘这是只有一个四十多岁的红衣军人在Ticonderoga.

930
01:00:34,099 --> 01:00:36,502
But there is one
Ethan Allen story that I’m...
但是这个有一个Ethan Allen的故事，我...

931
01:00:36,517 --> 01:00:37,819
– STANTON: No!
– .. very partial to...
– STANTON: 不！
– ..非常偏爱...

932
01:00:37,955 --> 01:00:40,604
No, you’re... you’re
going to tell a story!
不，你是...你是
要讲故事吗！

933
01:00:41,077 --> 01:00:43,480
I don’t believe... that I can bear...
我不相信...我能容忍...

934
01:00:43,584 --> 01:00:46,285
to listen to another one
of your stories right now!
现在去听你的另一个故事！

935
01:00:46,346 --> 01:00:49,280
STANTON: I need the B&O sideyard
schedules for Alexandria!
STANTON:我需要 Alexandria的B&O sideyard时间表！

936
01:00:49,325 --> 01:00:50,922
I asked for them this morning!
我在今天早上问过他们！

937
01:00:50,947 --> 01:00:52,947
[Lincoln laughing]

938
01:00:53,505 --> 01:00:57,569
It was right after the Revolution,
right after peace had been concluded,
这是对的在革命之后，
在和平结束时候是对的，

939
01:00:57,713 --> 01:00:59,180
and, hum...
那么，嗯...

940
01:00:59,474 --> 01:01:01,958
Ethan Allen went to London to help our
Ethan Allen来伦敦去帮助我们

941
01:01:02,071 --> 01:01:04,726
new country conduct
its business with the king.
和国王一起引导新国家的经济。

942
01:01:05,993 --> 01:01:08,689
The English sneered at how rough we are,
这个英国人会嘲笑我们如何粗鲁，

943
01:01:08,700 --> 01:01:11,388
and rude and simple-minded
and on like that,
没礼貌和头脑简单，就像那样，

944
01:01:11,422 --> 01:01:15,064
everywhere he went, till one day
he was invited to the townhouse
他去过每一个地方，直到一天他被邀请进入市政府

945
01:01:15,359 --> 01:01:17,292
of a great English lord.
一个伟大的英国贵族的。

946
01:01:19,607 --> 01:01:22,561
Dinner was served, beverages imbibed,
度过了晚宴，喝点饮料，

947
01:01:23,308 --> 01:01:25,710
time passed, as happens, and
随着时间流逝

948
01:01:25,859 --> 01:01:28,123
Mr. Allen found he needed the privy.
Allen先生发现他需要它。

949
01:01:30,008 --> 01:01:32,617
He was grateful to be directed thence.
他从那个时候起被控制起来。

950
01:01:36,113 --> 01:01:38,136
Relieved, you might say.
也许，你可能会讲。

951
01:01:38,161 --> 01:01:40,161
[Everyone laughs]

952
01:01:40,500 --> 01:01:43,837
Now, Mr. Allen discovered
现在，Allen发现

953
01:01:43,951 --> 01:01:47,898
on entering the water closet that
the only decoration therein was a...
在进入洗手间的时候，他发现其中唯一的装饰是一个...

954
01:01:47,968 --> 01:01:50,306
a portrait of George Washington.
乔治 华盛顿的肖像画。

955
01:01:54,011 --> 01:01:56,480
Ethan Allen done what he came to do,
Ethan Allen做完他要做的事情，

956
01:01:56,526 --> 01:01:59,542
and returned to the drawing room.
然后回到了休息室。

957
01:01:59,804 --> 01:02:01,755
His host and the others were disappointed
东道主和其他人都非常的失望

958
01:02:01,767 --> 01:02:03,774
when he didn’t mention
Washington’s portrait.
当他没有说起华盛顿的肖像画的时候。

959
01:02:03,798 --> 01:02:05,546
And finally His Lordship couldn’t resist,
最终贵族大人没有忍住，

960
01:02:05,580 --> 01:02:07,548
and asked Mr. Allen had he noticed it,
问了Allen先生的评价，

961
01:02:07,576 --> 01:02:09,978
the picture of Washington. He had.
他拥有的华盛顿的肖像画。

962
01:02:10,084 --> 01:02:14,946
What did he think of its placement, did it
seem appropriately located to Mr. Allen?
他对它的位置有什么意见，有没有可以安排给Allen先生安排的工作？

963
01:02:14,990 --> 01:02:16,552
Mr. Allen said it did.
Mr. Allen 说这些.

964
01:02:17,146 --> 01:02:20,249
His host was astounded!
Appropriate?
东道主非常的吃惊！
合适的？

965
01:02:20,897 --> 01:02:23,983
George Washington’s likeness
in a water closet?
乔治 华盛顿的肖像画在洗手间里面？

966
01:02:23,995 --> 01:02:27,362
Yes, said Mr. Allen, where
it’ll do good service.
是的，Allen先生说，在那里它给做良好的服务。

967
01:02:28,119 --> 01:02:30,499
The whole world knows
nothing’ll make an Englishman shit
整个世界都知道，没有东西可以使一个英国男人讨厌

968
01:02:30,515 --> 01:02:32,917
quicker than the sight
of George Washington.
超过乔治 华盛顿。

969
01:02:32,942 --> 01:02:34,942
[Everyone laughs]

970
01:02:36,950 --> 01:02:38,751
I love that story.
我喜欢这个故事。

971
01:02:40,876 --> 01:02:46,876
[Cable telegraph clicking]

972
01:03:05,491 --> 01:03:07,894
CHARLES BENJAMIN: Fort Fisher
is ours. We’ve taken the port.
CHARLES BENJAMIN: 费血堡是我们的了，我们拿下了它。

973
01:03:07,941 --> 01:03:09,424
WELLES: And Wilmington?
WELLES:Wilmington怎么样？

974
01:03:11,680 --> 01:03:15,431
ECKERT: We’ve taken the fort, but the
city of Wilmington has not surrendered.
ECKERT:我们已经那些了那个城堡，但是Wilmington还没有投降。

975
01:03:15,886 --> 01:03:17,707
STANTON: How many casualties?
STANTON: 人员伤亡怎么样？

976
01:03:30,104 --> 01:03:32,189
– FERNANDO WOOD: Heavy losses.
– GEORGE PENDLETON: And more to come.
– FERNANDO WOOD: 损失惨重。
– GEORGE PENDLETON:未来还有更多。

977
01:03:32,230 --> 01:03:33,769
WOOD: Sours the national mood.
WOOD: 糟糕的国民情绪。

978
01:03:33,840 --> 01:03:36,473
That might suffice to discourage him...
– PENDLETON: To bring this down?
这个可能能够足够阻止他....
– PENDLETON: 把这些停止吗？

979
01:03:36,741 --> 01:03:39,304
Not in a fight like this.
This is to the death.
没有一个战争像这样。
这是在制造死亡。

980
01:03:39,384 --> 01:03:40,835
WOOD: It’s gruesome!
WOOD: 这是非常可怕的！

981
01:03:41,189 --> 01:03:43,331
PENDLETON: Are you despairing,
or merely lazy?
PENDLETON: 你感觉到了绝望了吗，或者
仅仅只是这样的？

982
01:03:43,784 --> 01:03:48,450
This fight is for The United States
of America. Nothing “suffices”!
这是为了整个美国的战斗，不是仅仅在满足谁的需要！

983
01:03:48,552 --> 01:03:50,124
A rumor? Nothing!
谣言吗？没事！

984
01:03:50,152 --> 01:03:53,093
They’re not lazy.
They’re busily buying votes!
他们并不懒惰。
他们正忙着在购买选票！

985
01:03:53,134 --> 01:03:55,826
While we hope to be saved
by “the national mood?!”
虽然我们希望可以拯救‘国民情绪’

986
01:04:02,231 --> 01:04:05,794
Before this blood is dry,
when Stevens next takes the floor,
在血液凝固之前，
当 Stevens下一个发言的时候，

987
01:04:05,877 --> 01:04:07,515
taunt him. You excel at that.
嘲笑他。你擅长做这些。

988
01:04:07,575 --> 01:04:11,436
Get him to proclaim what we all know
he believes in his coal-colored heart:
让他去宣传那些我们都知道的
他用他那颗黑色的心里面相信的：

989
01:04:11,472 --> 01:04:15,622
that this vote is meant to set the
black race on high, to niggerate America.
这个投票时为了提高黑色人种的地位，为了美国黑人。

990
01:04:15,668 --> 01:04:18,071
WOOD: George, please. Stay on course.
WOOD:乔治，请。待在这里。

991
01:04:18,884 --> 01:04:21,286
PENDLETON: Bring Stevens to full froth.
PENDLETON: 许给Stevens那些无意义的空谈

992
01:04:21,716 --> 01:04:24,809
I can ensure that every newspaperman
from Louisville to San Francisco
我能确定所有从Louisville到San Francisco的报社记者

993
01:04:24,841 --> 01:04:26,754
will be here to witness it and print it.
将在这里见证和出版它。

994
01:04:29,887 --> 01:04:32,371
SCHUYLER COLFAX: The floor
belongs to the mellifluent gentleman
SCHUYLER COLFAX:发言权是属于上等的绅士的

995
01:04:32,389 --> 01:04:35,022
from Kentucky,
Mr. George Yeaman.
来自Kentucky，
Mr. George Yeaman.

996
01:04:40,695 --> 01:04:43,097
YEAMAN: I thank you, Speaker Colfax.
YEAMAN: 我很感激你，Colfax议长。

997
01:04:50,562 --> 01:04:54,735
Although... I’m disgusted by slavery
尽管...我非常的厌恶奴隶制

998
01:04:58,429 --> 01:05:01,069
I rise on this sad and solemn day.
我在这个悲伤，严肃的日子里。

999
01:05:01,645 --> 01:05:04,667
to announce that I’m
opposed to the amendment.
宣布我反对修正法案。

1000
01:05:09,551 --> 01:05:12,708
We must consider what
will become of colored folk
我们必须考虑我们将变成一个多色彩的种族

1001
01:05:13,165 --> 01:05:17,355
if four million are in
one instant set free.
如果四百万的黑人立即被释放。

1002
01:05:17,553 --> 01:05:20,556
LITTON: They’ll be free, George.
That’s what’ll become of them!
LITTON: 他们将自由，乔治。
这将会变成什么样！

1003
01:05:21,242 --> 01:05:25,571
SCHELL: Think how splendid
if Mr. Yeaman switched.
SCHELL: 想想多么的辉煌吧，如果 Yeaman先生转变了。

1004
01:05:25,838 --> 01:05:28,635
LATHAM: Too publicly against us.
He can’t change course now.
LATHAM: 太多的人反抗我们。
他不能改变现状。

1005
01:05:28,893 --> 01:05:31,826
BILBO: Not for some
miserable little job anyways.
BILBO: 不管怎么样，不是为了一些小小的可怜的家伙工作的。

1006
01:05:32,433 --> 01:05:36,630
我们将被迫释放
男人的有色种族
We will be forced to enfranchise
the men of the colored race.

1007
01:05:37,770 --> 01:05:39,988
这将不再是不人道的
It would be inhuman not to!

1008
01:05:40,443 --> 01:05:43,805
在我们周围的人准备给黑人投票
Who among us is prepared
to give Negroes the vote?

1009
01:05:45,180 --> 01:05:46,880
[boos throughout the chamber]
YEAMAN: And, and!
嘘声响亮整个教室

1010
01:05:47,046 --> 01:05:48,999
对于那应该遵循什么
What shall follow upon that?

1011
01:05:50,012 --> 01:05:52,199
全体解放
Universal enfranchisement?

1012
01:05:53,343 --> 01:05:55,053
抽票给你女人？
Votes for women?

