1757
02:05:28,875 --> 02:05:31,277
LINCOLN: I’d like peace immediately.
我希望我们立刻议和

1758
02:05:31,392 --> 02:05:32,954
STEPHENS: Yes, and...?
那么...？

1759
02:05:35,745 --> 02:05:38,147
LINCOLN: I’d like your states restored
我希望南方诸州

1760
02:05:38,170 --> 02:05:41,912
to their practical relations
to the Union immediately.
能够立刻恢复先前在合众国中的地位

1761
02:05:45,066 --> 02:05:49,141
If this could be given me in writing,
as Vice President of the Confederacy,
如果能在条约内加上这一项，
作为南方邦联的副总统

1762
02:05:49,142 --> 02:05:53,897
I’d bring that document
with celerity to Jefferson Davis.
我将以最快速度将文件
递交给Jefferson Davis 总统

1763
02:05:55,483 --> 02:05:59,594
SEWARD: Surrender, and
we can discuss reconstruction.
投降，然后我们再谈重建的问题

1764
02:06:01,292 --> 02:06:03,694
Surrender won’t be thought of
除非你们能以书面形式

1765
02:06:03,787 --> 02:06:06,393
unless you’ve assured us, in writing,
让我们保证及时恢复我们

1766
02:06:06,526 --> 02:06:09,529
that we’ll be readmitted in
time to block this amendment.
以抵制这项修正案的生效的话，
我们便不考虑议和

1767
02:06:09,990 --> 02:06:13,868
HUNTER: This is the arrogant
demand of a conqueror.
对于胜利方来说提出这样的请求
未免有些傲慢自大了吧

1768
02:06:13,894 --> 02:06:18,146
SEWARD: You’ll not be a conquered
people, Mr. Hunter, you will be citizens.
你们并非被战败方，Hunter先生，
你们仍是美国公民

1769
02:06:19,210 --> 02:06:22,476
Returned to the laws and the
guarantees of rights of the Constitution.
重新受到法律的束缚
并获得宪法保障的公民权利

1770
02:06:23,126 --> 02:06:27,906
Which now extinguishes slavery.
And with it our economy.
宪法现在废除了奴隶制，
我们的经济

1771
02:06:28,753 --> 02:06:32,036
All our laws will be determined by
a Congress of vengeful Yankees,
我们的法律
都由一群心怀不满的北方人所决定

1772
02:06:32,602 --> 02:06:35,727
all our rights’ll be subject
to a Supreme Court
我们的所有权利都将受到最高法院的管制

1773
02:06:35,983 --> 02:06:38,385
benched by Black Republican radicals.
里面坐满了共和党的黑人激进分子

1774
02:06:38,612 --> 02:06:41,791
All our traditions will be obliterated.
我们的传统将不复存在

1775
02:06:42,656 --> 02:06:44,546
We won’t know ourselves anymore.
我们都不再记得自己曾经是谁了

1776
02:06:46,285 --> 02:06:48,825
We ain’t here to discuss reconstruction,
我们不是来谈重建事宜的

1777
02:06:48,838 --> 02:06:51,478
we have no legal basis
for that discussion.
关于这点我们没有法律基础

1778
02:06:51,513 --> 02:06:52,980
But I don’t want to deal falsely.
但我不想做虚伪的交易

1779
02:06:53,051 --> 02:06:55,453
The Northern states’ll ratify,
most of ‘em.
北方诸州中的大多数
会让这一修正案生效的

1780
02:06:55,656 --> 02:06:58,633
As I figure, it remains for two of
the Southern states to do the same,
据我统计，南方还有两个州亟待执行法案

1781
02:06:58,655 --> 02:07:00,666
even after all are readmitted.
即便在所有的州重新加入联邦之后也一样

1782
02:07:00,823 --> 02:07:02,417
And I been working on that.
我会为之采取进一步举措的

1783
02:07:02,942 --> 02:07:04,159
Tennessee and Louisiana.
田纳西州和路易斯安那州

1784
02:07:04,464 --> 02:07:06,867
Arkansas too, most likely.
It’ll be ratified.
阿肯萨斯州也有可能

1785
02:07:07,328 --> 02:07:10,264
Slavery, sir... it’s done.
至于奴隶制，先生...已经结束了

1786
02:07:23,526 --> 02:07:26,653
If we submit ourselves to law, Alex,
如果我们把自身交由法律管束，Alex

1787
02:07:26,929 --> 02:07:29,547
even submit to losing freedoms...
哪怕就此失去一些自由

1788
02:07:30,333 --> 02:07:32,735
the freedom to oppress, for instance...
比如，失去压迫他人的自由

1789
02:07:33,736 --> 02:07:37,464
we may discover other freedoms
previously unknown to us.
我们或许能发现
其它前所未见的自由权利

1790
02:07:38,231 --> 02:07:41,489
Had you kept faith with
democratic process,
你们还相信民主进程

1791
02:07:41,668 --> 02:07:44,671
as frustrating as that can be...
– CAMPBELL: Come sir,
够了，先生

1792
02:07:44,828 --> 02:07:47,117
spare us at least these pieties.
收起这套虚伪的面孔吧

1793
02:07:48,246 --> 02:07:50,511
Did you defeat us with ballots?
你们以选举的方式击败了我们吗？

1794
02:07:51,577 --> 02:07:53,907
STEPHENS: How’ve you held your Union together?
你们是怎样将联邦团结起来的？

1795
02:07:54,284 --> 02:07:55,578
Through democracy?
通过民主？

1796
02:07:56,592 --> 02:08:00,195
How many hundreds of thousands
have died during your administration?
在您的任期内究竟死了多少人？

1797
02:08:01,228 --> 02:08:03,630
Your Union, sir, is bonded
in cannon fire and death.
您的联邦，先生，是由炮火和鲜血堆积的

1798
02:08:07,566 --> 02:08:09,404
LINCOLN: It may be you’re right.
也许你说的对

1799
02:08:13,570 --> 02:08:18,565
But say all we done is show
the world that democracy isn’t chaos,
但我们所做的一切皆是在向世界昭示，
民主并非暴乱

1800
02:08:21,477 --> 02:08:26,590
that there is a great invisible
strength in a people’s union?
在人民的联邦间
存在一种伟大的力量将其维系吗？

1801
02:08:27,184 --> 02:08:32,407
Say we’ve shown that a people can
endure awful sacrifice and yet cohere?
然而人民在做出巨大的牺牲之后
不是仍旧团结一致吗？

1802
02:08:33,457 --> 02:08:37,427
Mightn’t that save at least the
idea of democracy to aspire to?
至少值得追求的民主
不是就此被拯救了吗？

1803
02:08:38,327 --> 02:08:40,730
Eventually, to become worthy of?
最终这一切不是都展现出其价值了吗

1804
02:08:44,853 --> 02:08:48,228
At all rates, whatever may be
proven by blood and sacrifice
无论如何，那些流血与牺牲所能证明的

1805
02:08:48,256 --> 02:08:50,659
must’ve been proved by now.
都已在当下得证

1806
02:09:01,044 --> 02:09:03,447
Shall we stop this bleeding?
我们可以停止这场流血的战争了吗？

1807
02:10:41,859 --> 02:10:45,188
LINCOLN: Once he surrenders, send
his boys back to their homes,
一旦他投降，
就把那些孩子送回他们的家

1808
02:10:45,411 --> 02:10:47,667
their farms, their shops.
他们的农庄，他们的作坊

1809
02:10:49,198 --> 02:10:52,637
GRANT: Yes sir... as we discussed.
好的，先生...就像我们之前说好的那样

1810
02:10:52,710 --> 02:10:56,407
LINCOLN: Liberality all around.
No punishment. I don’t want that.
所有的人都将获得自由，没有惩罚，
我不想看到

1811
02:10:57,070 --> 02:10:59,728
And the leaders -Jeff
and the rest of ‘em...
那些领头人——Jeff还有剩下的那些
...

1812
02:10:59,862 --> 02:11:01,986
if they escape, leave the
country while my back’s turned,
如果他们在我不注意时逃离了这个国家

1813
02:11:01,989 --> 02:11:04,035
that wouldn’t upset me none.
那才是我会感担心的事

1814
02:11:05,054 --> 02:11:07,812
When peace comes
it mustn’t just be hangings.
我们追求的是真正而非表面的和平

1815
02:11:14,230 --> 02:11:16,130
By outward appearance,
从外表上看

1816
02:11:17,499 --> 02:11:20,053
you’re ten years older
than you were a year ago.
您比一年前要老了十岁

1817
02:11:23,669 --> 02:11:26,547
Some weariness has bit at my bones.
我身上的每一块骨头都感觉极度疲惫

1818
02:11:39,282 --> 02:11:43,291
I never seen the like of it before.
What I seen today.
我今天看到的一切
给了我从没有过的感觉

1819
02:11:45,248 --> 02:11:47,650
Never seen the like of it before.
从没有过

1820
02:11:49,496 --> 02:11:54,003
GRANT: You always knew that...
what this was going to be.
你知道的...它接下来会如何发展

1821
02:11:55,626 --> 02:11:58,029
Intimate, and ugly.
美好却又丑陋

1822
02:12:01,021 --> 02:12:04,646
You must’ve needed to see it close
when you decided to come down here.
在你决定来这里之前你一定急需想看看这幅画面

1823
02:12:23,404 --> 02:12:26,757
LINCOLN: We’ve made it possible
for one another to do terrible things.
我们让自相残杀变得可能

1824
02:12:29,517 --> 02:12:31,509
GRANT: And we’ve won the war.
并且我们赢得了这场战争的胜利

1825
02:12:31,988 --> 02:12:35,356
Now you have to lead us out of it.
现在你不许带领我们走出它

1826
02:14:07,203 --> 02:14:08,939
You’ve an itch to travel?
你想去旅行吗

1827
02:14:10,378 --> 02:14:11,940
I’d like that.
我很乐意

1828
02:14:12,543 --> 02:14:14,603
To the West by rail.
搭乘火车去西部

1829
02:14:14,878 --> 02:14:17,280
 Overseas.
去海外吧

1830
02:14:18,469 --> 02:14:20,030
The Holy Land.
去圣地

1831
02:14:22,822 --> 02:14:27,410
Awfully pious for a man who takes
his wife out buggy-riding on Good Friday.
在耶稣的受难日带着妻子坐马车出行的男人要是多么虔诚的信徒

1832
02:14:27,634 --> 02:14:29,196
Jerusalem.
耶路撒冷

1833
02:14:29,353 --> 02:14:31,456
Where David and Solomon walked.
那David 和Solomon走过的土地

1834
02:14:31,637 --> 02:14:35,396
I dream of... walking
in that ancient city.
我梦想着...漫步在那座古城中

1835
02:14:41,178 --> 02:14:45,640
All anyone will remember of me is
I was crazy and I ruined your happiness.
每个人都会记得我是那样疯狂并
毁掉了你的幸福

1836
02:14:46,439 --> 02:14:49,705
Anyone thinks that
doesn’t understand, Molly.
那样想的人是不会理解我们的，Molly

1837
02:14:52,791 --> 02:14:54,362
When they look at you,
当他们看着你的时候

1838
02:14:55,841 --> 02:14:58,748
at what it cost to live
at the heart of this,
他们会好奇，带着这样的一颗心生活

1839
02:15:00,279 --> 02:15:03,340
they’ll wonder at it. They’ll
wonder at you, they should.
他们会好奇的，他们也理应好奇

1840
02:15:05,178 --> 02:15:07,975
But they should also look
at the wretched woman by your side,
他们理所应当看看身边这个不幸的女人

1841
02:15:07,994 --> 02:15:10,396
if they want to understand
what this was truly like.
如果他们想知道这些的话

1842
02:15:12,079 --> 02:15:16,111
For the ordinary person.
For anyone other than you.
为了人民，
为了你之外的所有人

1843
02:15:16,170 --> 02:15:18,169
We must try to be happier.
我们必须试着变得快乐

1844
02:15:18,731 --> 02:15:20,774
We must. Both of us.
我们必须这么做，我俩都是

1845
02:15:21,110 --> 02:15:23,512
We’ve been so miserable for so long.
我们过了这么久悲惨的日子

1846
02:15:32,647 --> 02:15:35,049
LINCOLN: I did say some colored men,
我确实讲到了一部分有色人种中的男性

1847
02:15:35,269 --> 02:15:39,959
the intelligent, the educated,
and veterans, I qualified it.
那些受过教育的，退伍军人，
我授予他们这项权利

1848
02:15:40,194 --> 02:15:43,523
ASHLEY: Mr. Stevens is furious,
he wants to know why you qualified it.
Stevens先生很生气，
他想知道您授予这项权利的原因

1849
02:15:43,598 --> 02:15:46,004
COLFAX: No one's heard the
intelligent or the educated part.
没人听说过“受过教育”这一部分

1850
02:15:46,037 --> 02:15:50,516
All they heard was the first time
any president has ever made mention
他们闻知的就是
史上第一次有总统提及

1851
02:15:50,787 --> 02:15:52,349
of Negro voting.
要给与黑人投票权

1852
02:15:52,597 --> 02:15:56,273
LINCOLN: Still, I wish I had
mentioned it in a better speech.
我希望我能在一次更好的演说中
提及这件事

1853
02:15:56,305 --> 02:15:59,932
ASHLEY: Mr. Stevens also wants to know
why you didn’t make a better speech.
Stevens先生也想知道
您为什么没有发表一次更出色的演说

1854
02:16:03,068 --> 02:16:04,878
NICOLAY: Mrs. Lincoln’s
waiting in the carriage.
林肯夫人在车上等您

1855
02:16:04,937 --> 02:16:06,527
She wants me to remind you of the hour,
她想我给您提醒一下时间

1856
02:16:06,544 --> 02:16:09,389
and that you’ll have to pick up
Miss Harris and Major Rathbone.
您还得去接Harris小姐和Rathbone市长

1857
02:16:13,311 --> 02:16:15,202
– LINCOLN: Am I in trouble?
我惹麻烦了吗
– SLADE: No, sir.
还没有

1858
02:16:15,397 --> 02:16:17,199
Thank you, Mr. Slade.
非常感谢你，slade先生

1859
02:16:32,437 --> 02:16:34,840
LINCOLN: I suppose it’s time to go,
我想我该走了

1860
02:16:35,371 --> 02:16:36,933
though I would rather stay.
尽管我更想呆在这里

1861
02:18:07,011 --> 02:18:09,487
OWNER OF THE THEATER:
The President has been shot!
总统遭到了枪击！

1862
02:18:12,572 --> 02:18:16,245
The President has been
shot at Ford’s Theater!
总统在福特剧院遭到了枪击！

1863
02:18:58,166 --> 02:19:01,471
DR. BARNES: It’s... 7:22 in the morning,
现在是...清晨七点二十二分

1864
02:19:02,541 --> 02:19:05,487
Saturday the 15th of April.
It’s all over.
四月十五日，周六，病人宣告死亡

1865
02:19:05,702 --> 02:19:08,105
The President is no more.
总统去世了

1866
02:19:10,777 --> 02:19:13,180
STANTON: Now he belongs to the ages.
现在他成了历史的一部分

1867
02:19:19,364 --> 02:19:24,695
LINCOLN: <i>Fondly do we hope,
fervently do we pray,</i>
我们天真地盼望，热诚地祷告

1868
02:19:26,165 --> 02:19:31,479
<i>that this mighty scourge of war
may speedily pass away.</i>
这场惩罚性的战争
已经迅速地远离我们远去

1869
02:19:34,318 --> 02:19:36,721
Yet, if God wills that it continue
然而，如果神执意让战争持续下去

1870
02:19:37,439 --> 02:19:41,112
until all the wealth piled by
the bondman's
直到从所有财富被奴隶堆积

1871
02:19:41,125 --> 02:19:46,104
two hundred and fifty years
of unrequited toil shall be sunk,
在这两百五十年间困苦劳动之下所累积的财富毁去

1872
02:19:47,435 --> 02:19:51,310
and until every drop of
blood drawn with the lash
直到每一滴血迹绘出的皮鞭

1873
02:19:51,424 --> 02:19:55,527
shall be paid by another
drawn with the sword,
被还请给下每一条冤魂

1874
02:19:56,544 --> 02:20:01,562
as was said three thousand years ago,
so still it must be said
就如古人在三千年前所说，
而今天仍要延叙

1875
02:20:02,059 --> 02:20:09,886
"the judgments of the Lord are
true and righteous altogether.”
主的审判信实，合乎公义

1876
02:20:14,993 --> 02:20:16,795
With malice toward none,
不以恶待人

1877
02:20:19,001 --> 02:20:21,403
with charity for all,
以宽容包容对人

1878
02:20:22,537 --> 02:20:26,515
with firmness in the right as
God gives us to see the right,
神开启我们的眼让我们看见公义

1879
02:20:26,554 --> 02:20:29,843
let us strive on to finish
the work we are in,
让我们全力以赴，完成我们所有的工作

1880
02:20:30,637 --> 02:20:33,040
to bind up the nation's wounds,
治疗国家的伤口

1881
02:20:34,096 --> 02:20:38,684
to care for him who shall
have borne the battle,
照料在战役中忍受苦痛的人

1882
02:20:40,701 --> 02:20:43,104
and for his widow and his orphan,
和那些寡妇、孤儿

1883
02:20:44,837 --> 02:20:49,385
to do all which may achieve and cherish
不忘记珍惜爱护他们

1884
02:20:50,152 --> 02:20:55,482
a just and a lasting peace among ourselves
让我们之间竭尽全力维持一个和平

1885
02:20:56,140 --> 02:20:58,812
and with all nations.
与所有的国家

1886
02:21:04,165 --> 02:21:10,171

